# Multimedia Production

Frameworks for video scripting, podcast production, visual content briefs, and cross-format content repurposing.

## Core Principle

**The medium shapes the message.** Every format has unique strengths and constraints. Effective multimedia production adapts the core idea to each format's native language rather than forcing a blog post into a video or a podcast into a carousel.

## Video Content

### Video Types and Parameters

| Type | Duration | Platform | Production Level | Goal |
|------|----------|----------|-----------------|------|
| Short-form (Reels/TikTok) | 15-90 sec | Instagram, TikTok, YouTube Shorts | Low-medium | Awareness, reach |
| Explainer | 2-5 min | YouTube, landing pages | Medium | Education, consideration |
| Tutorial | 5-15 min | YouTube, course platform | Medium-high | Skill-building, authority |
| Webinar | 30-60 min | Zoom, LinkedIn Live | Medium | Lead generation, depth |
| Brand story | 1-3 min | Website, social | High | Trust, emotional connection |
| Testimonial | 1-3 min | Website, sales enablement | Medium | Social proof, conversion |

### Video Script Template

```markdown
## Video Script: [Title]
**Duration:** [Target length]
**Platform:** [Primary distribution channel]
**Objective:** [What should the viewer do after watching?]

### Hook (0:00-0:10)
[Opening line: bold claim, surprising stat, or direct question]
VISUAL: [What the viewer sees]
AUDIO: [Background music or sound direction]

### Context (0:10-0:30)
[Why this matters to the viewer right now]
VISUAL: [Talking head, text overlay, or B-roll]

### Main Content
#### Point 1: [Key idea] (0:30-X:XX)
SCRIPT: [Spoken words]
VISUAL: [Screen share, animation, or demonstration]
TRANSITION: [How to bridge to point 2]

#### Point 2: [Key idea] (X:XX-X:XX)
SCRIPT: [Spoken words]
VISUAL: [Supporting visuals]

#### Point 3: [Key idea] (X:XX-X:XX)
SCRIPT: [Spoken words]
VISUAL: [Supporting visuals]

### Summary (X:XX-X:XX)
[Recap the three key takeaways in one sentence each]

### CTA (final 10-15 sec)
[Clear next step: subscribe, download, visit link in description]
VISUAL: [End screen with subscribe button and related video]
```

## Podcast Production

### Episode Planning Framework

| Phase | Activities | Timeline |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Topic Selection | Audience demand research, guest availability, editorial calendar alignment | 2-3 weeks before |
| Pre-production | Guest research, question list, technical setup check | 5-7 days before |
| Recording | Audio capture, backup recording, timestamped notes | Record day |
| Post-production | Editing, mixing, mastering, transcript generation | 2-3 days after |
| Asset Creation | Show notes, audiogram clips, quote graphics, blog summary | 1-2 days after edit |
| Publishing | Episode upload, metadata, distribution to platforms | Publish day |
| Promotion | Social posts, newsletter inclusion, guest cross-promotion | Publish day + 7 days |

