## Content Repurposing

### Repurposing Workflow

```text
PILLAR CONTENT (e.g., 3,000-word guide)
    │
    ├── Extract → 5-10 social posts (key stats, quotes, tips)
    ├── Condense → 1 email newsletter section (300 words)
    ├── Visualize → 1 infographic or carousel (key framework)
    ├── Record → 1 video summary (3-5 min explainer)
    ├── Discuss → 1 podcast segment (10-15 min deep dive)
    ├── Atomize → 3-5 tweet/thread ideas
    └── Gate → 1 downloadable resource (checklist, template)
```

### Format Adaptation Guidelines

| From | To | Adaptation Notes |
|------|----|-----------------|
| Blog post | Video script | Lead with the hook; cut setup by 50%; add visual direction |
| Blog post | Social carousel | One slide per key point; max 10 slides; end with CTA |
| Podcast | Blog post | Structure around key quotes; add context and links |
| Webinar | Blog series | One post per major section; add depth lost in live format |
| Research report | Infographic | Highlight 3-5 most surprising findings; simplify data viz |
| Case study | Testimonial clips | Pull 2-3 strongest outcome quotes; add context overlay |

## Common Pitfalls

```text
- Copy-paste repurposing: Dumping a blog post transcript into a video script without adapting
- Ignoring platform norms: Posting the same content identically across all channels
- Over-producing: Investing in high production value when the audience values authenticity
- No hook: Starting videos or podcasts with lengthy introductions instead of immediate value
- Missing accessibility: No captions on video, no transcripts for podcasts, no alt text on graphics
- Orphaned assets: Creating multimedia content without linking back to pillar content for SEO value
```
